1
00:00:10,350 --> 00:00:11,046
<i>Previously on From...</i>

2
00:00:11,177 --> 00:00:12,221
[Sara] I hear their voices.

3
00:00:12,352 --> 00:00:14,658
They said it was
the only way to go home.

4
00:00:14,789 --> 00:00:16,399
Sara, just tell me
what you did.

5
00:00:16,530 --> 00:00:18,314
[Sara]
I left the door open.

6
00:00:18,445 --> 00:00:19,576
[Weeping]

7
00:00:19,707 --> 00:00:21,448
Are you living in town
or Colony House?

8
00:00:21,578 --> 00:00:22,840
-Town.
-Julie.

9
00:00:22,971 --> 00:00:24,407
Colony House.

10
00:00:24,538 --> 00:00:25,539
Why are you doing this?

11
00:00:25,669 --> 00:00:26,757
[Fatima] What's wrong?

12
00:00:26,888 --> 00:00:29,978
I think maybe
I-I made a mistake.

13
00:00:30,109 --> 00:00:33,895
[Fatima] Julie, there are
no mistakes, just choices,

14
00:00:34,026 --> 00:00:35,810
and you chose what was right
for you, and that matters.

15
00:00:35,940 --> 00:00:37,594
Come on,
try it out!

16
00:00:37,725 --> 00:00:39,422
[Kenny] Every single one
of these pins

17
00:00:39,553 --> 00:00:40,902
is a different resident
who drove in

18
00:00:41,033 --> 00:00:42,469
from a different location.

19
00:00:42,599 --> 00:00:45,559
That is fucking impossible.

20
00:00:45,689 --> 00:00:49,563
I don't just sit around,
accepting the world as it is!

21
00:00:49,693 --> 00:00:51,695
-[Static hisses on radio]
-Someone is doing this,

22
00:00:51,826 --> 00:00:53,480
and I'm not gonna rest
until I figure out how!

23
00:00:53,610 --> 00:00:54,872
[Father] I wish you had
the luxury of grief,

24
00:00:55,003 --> 00:00:56,526
but you don't, Boyd.

25
00:00:56,657 --> 00:00:58,920
These people need you.

26
00:00:59,051 --> 00:01:01,792
You need to be the one
to lead these people home.

27
00:01:01,923 --> 00:01:04,143
'Cause if you don't?
She died for nothing.

28
00:01:04,273 --> 00:01:06,928
What are you doing here?
You promised you'd stay home.

29
00:01:07,059 --> 00:01:08,625
If I didn't show up,
they would have wondered why.

30
00:01:08,756 --> 00:01:10,366
-It'll be okay.
-Sara...

31
00:01:10,497 --> 00:01:11,976
I promise.

32
00:01:12,107 --> 00:01:13,848
Do you wanna help me bring
over the rest of the food?

33
00:01:13,978 --> 00:01:15,371
Yeah!

34
00:01:16,633 --> 00:01:20,028
[Jim]
I just feel so... broken.

35
00:01:20,159 --> 00:01:22,378
We're gonna figure it
out together.

36
00:01:22,509 --> 00:01:23,727
Don't worry.

37
00:01:23,858 --> 00:01:24,728
Whatcha got there?

38
00:01:24,859 --> 00:01:25,860
Sweet potatoes.

39
00:01:25,990 --> 00:01:27,383
Ooh!

40
00:01:27,514 --> 00:01:30,430
Nice family.

41
00:01:30,560 --> 00:01:34,521
[Gasping breaths]

42
00:01:43,573 --> 00:01:44,879
[Ethan] Sara!

43
00:01:45,009 --> 00:01:46,185
[Boyd] Hey.
Oh! Oh, no, no, no.

44
00:01:46,315 --> 00:01:47,795
Okay, grab her,
grab her arm, grab her arm!

45
00:01:47,925 --> 00:01:49,405
Hold on, hold on!

46
00:01:54,715 --> 00:01:58,458
[Goats bleating]

47
00:01:58,588 --> 00:02:01,635
Hey, Alma. Come on.

48
00:02:01,765 --> 00:02:05,682
There you go, Alma,
a fresh batch just for you.

49
00:02:05,813 --> 00:02:08,685
Hey!
Make sure you share this time.

50
00:02:08,816 --> 00:02:12,559
Nathan! Nathan!

51
00:02:12,689 --> 00:02:15,562
It's your sister!
Something happened at the diner.

52
00:02:15,692 --> 00:02:16,824
They're taking her
to the clinic.

53
00:02:24,701 --> 00:02:26,834
I really am feeling much better.

54
00:02:26,964 --> 00:02:29,619
I still think you should spend
the night for observation, okay?

55
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:30,838
Do I have to?

56
00:02:30,968 --> 00:02:32,100
It's just,
with things like this,

57
00:02:32,231 --> 00:02:35,103
it's best not to
take any chances, you know?

58
00:02:35,234 --> 00:02:36,670
I can have someone
go get Nathan.

59
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:38,585
He can stay with you.

60
00:02:38,715 --> 00:02:42,763
No. He worries.
If he comes by,

61
00:02:42,893 --> 00:02:46,549
could you...
just tell him I'm sleeping.

62
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:47,724
Yeah, no problem.

63
00:02:47,855 --> 00:02:50,466
[Door opening, closing]

64
00:02:54,731 --> 00:02:55,863
I'll, uh...
I'll be right back, okay?

65
00:03:05,177 --> 00:03:08,092
Hey. How's she doing?

66
00:03:08,223 --> 00:03:10,007
I mean, fine,
given the circumstances.

67
00:03:10,138 --> 00:03:13,141
Has this happened before?

68
00:03:13,272 --> 00:03:15,709
Well, I mean,
not according to Sara.

69
00:03:15,839 --> 00:03:17,841
And unless there's an MRI
machine tucked around somewhere,

70
00:03:17,972 --> 00:03:19,713
there's no way to really
know what's going on.

71
00:03:19,843 --> 00:03:21,410
-Yeah.
-I'm, uh...

72
00:03:21,541 --> 00:03:23,673
I'm gonna keep her overnight
and see if anything changes.

73
00:03:23,804 --> 00:03:26,023
Okay. You sure you're ready
for that?

74
00:03:26,154 --> 00:03:28,069
Look, I don't know
how that door got open,

75
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,984
but I'm not gonna
let those things

76
00:03:30,114 --> 00:03:31,986
take this place
away from me.

77
00:03:32,116 --> 00:03:33,857
They've already taken
too much already.

78
00:03:33,988 --> 00:03:37,121
Yeah. They sure have.

79
00:03:37,252 --> 00:03:39,776
Hey, can I ask
you a question?

80
00:03:39,907 --> 00:03:43,780
These seizures - first,
the Matthews kid, now Sara.

81
00:03:43,911 --> 00:03:45,129
You think it's possible

82
00:03:45,260 --> 00:03:47,219
to have a physical
reaction to this place?

83
00:03:47,349 --> 00:03:50,178
Maybe something you
might normally diagnose

84
00:03:50,309 --> 00:03:52,049
as one thing on the outside,
but here it's...

85
00:03:52,180 --> 00:03:55,052
Look, Boyd, if you asked me
this six months ago,

86
00:03:55,183 --> 00:03:57,098
I would have said anything that
we've seen here was impossible.

87
00:03:57,229 --> 00:03:59,753
But the truth is, I...

88
00:03:59,883 --> 00:04:03,583
Okay, how long has
this been going on for?

89
00:04:05,889 --> 00:04:08,022
Long enough that it's got me
asking stupid questions.

90
00:04:08,152 --> 00:04:09,980
-Boyd...
-I'm fine.

91
00:04:10,111 --> 00:04:12,809
Come by tomorrow.
I want to take a look at it.

92
00:04:12,940 --> 00:04:14,594
No need.
I already know what it is.

93
00:04:17,031 --> 00:04:18,989
Nathan's here.

94
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,513
[Sighing]
She doesn't want to see him.

95
00:04:22,819 --> 00:04:23,951
Yeah, I don't... I don't know.

96
00:04:25,866 --> 00:04:27,998
Um, okay.
Go take care of your patient.

97
00:04:28,129 --> 00:04:29,826
I got this, okay?

98
00:04:29,957 --> 00:04:32,916
And I'm good.

99
00:04:33,047 --> 00:04:35,179
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Whoa!

100
00:04:35,310 --> 00:04:36,703
Is she okay?

101
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:38,487
She's fine.
She's sleeping.

102
00:04:40,054 --> 00:04:42,143
I wanna see her.

103
00:04:42,274 --> 00:04:44,188
And you will, tomorrow.

104
00:04:44,319 --> 00:04:45,842
Kristi's gonna sit
with her tonight

105
00:04:45,973 --> 00:04:47,017
and make sure
everything is okay.

106
00:04:47,148 --> 00:04:48,758
No, no. I-I need
to see her now, please.

107
00:04:48,889 --> 00:04:50,456
You will. Hey, hey.

108
00:04:50,586 --> 00:04:52,893
Is there anything else going on
that we should know about?

109
00:04:53,023 --> 00:04:56,723
Anything that might help Kristi
figure out what's wrong?

110
00:04:56,853 --> 00:04:58,855
No. I'm just worried,
that's all.

111
00:04:58,986 --> 00:05:01,075
She's my little sister.

112
00:05:01,205 --> 00:05:05,775
Right. Look,

113
00:05:05,906 --> 00:05:09,779
this is Kristi's first
night back since... right?

114
00:05:09,910 --> 00:05:11,346
We don't want
to be going in there

115
00:05:11,477 --> 00:05:14,697
and making tonight more
stressful than it already is.

116
00:05:14,828 --> 00:05:16,786
Sara's in good hands.
Okay?

117
00:05:16,917 --> 00:05:19,136
Go home.
Get some sleep.

118
00:05:19,267 --> 00:05:20,790
You'll see her in the morning.

119
00:05:20,921 --> 00:05:22,183
Yeah.

120
00:05:22,314 --> 00:05:23,793
Okay?

121
00:05:40,027 --> 00:05:44,118
Is Sara gonna be okay?

122
00:05:44,248 --> 00:05:46,163
Well, yeah,
she's down at the clinic.

123
00:05:46,294 --> 00:05:47,730
They're gonna take
good care of her. Don't worry.

124
00:05:47,861 --> 00:05:49,341
You remember Kristi?

125
00:05:49,471 --> 00:05:52,387
The nice lady
who took care of your leg?

126
00:05:52,518 --> 00:05:55,695
She's gonna patch up Sara
the same way she patched you up.

127
00:05:55,825 --> 00:05:59,002
In the meantime,

128
00:05:59,133 --> 00:06:01,614
we are gonna
play a little game.

129
00:06:01,744 --> 00:06:04,834
For you.

130
00:06:04,965 --> 00:06:06,793
Well, we said we're gonna
figure it out, right?

131
00:06:06,923 --> 00:06:09,012
Let's figure it out.
Follow me.

132
00:06:10,797 --> 00:06:11,972
[Exhales]

133
00:06:17,107 --> 00:06:18,282
We're gonna do some
problem-solving,

134
00:06:18,413 --> 00:06:20,023
and the way
you problem solve

135
00:06:20,154 --> 00:06:21,808
is by asking questions.

136
00:06:21,938 --> 00:06:25,028
You ask every question
that might apply,

137
00:06:25,159 --> 00:06:27,291
no matter how crazy,
no matter how unlikely.

138
00:06:27,422 --> 00:06:30,033
You put it up on a board,
you get it out in front of you

139
00:06:30,164 --> 00:06:31,948
so that you can identify
everything you know

140
00:06:32,079 --> 00:06:34,081
and everything you don't.

141
00:06:34,211 --> 00:06:36,997
It'll be like telling
a story.

142
00:06:37,127 --> 00:06:40,740
Right, buddy?
Question number one.

143
00:06:42,959 --> 00:06:44,874
[Ethan] Dad!

144
00:06:45,005 --> 00:06:47,660
What? You never wanted
to write on a wall?

145
00:06:57,234 --> 00:07:01,151
There.
That's where we begin.

