00:27:59,800 --> 00:28:03,325
I think that's what made him
such an effective preacher.

525
00:28:03,456 --> 00:28:07,416
Anyway, I could tell
my mother was afraid.

526
00:28:07,547 --> 00:28:10,202
My brothers had run to the door
and now they were shouting too,

527
00:28:10,332 --> 00:28:14,162
and my mother just kept
saying "Hide, hide."

528
00:28:14,293 --> 00:28:17,426
But I just stood there,
I couldn't move,

529
00:28:17,557 --> 00:28:20,168
because it was all so strange.

530
00:28:20,299 --> 00:28:24,520
I mean, we were just laughing
so hard, you know?

531
00:28:24,651 --> 00:28:27,219
It was gonna be
the best birthday ever.

532
00:28:27,349 --> 00:28:29,395
The sun was so bright
coming in through the door

533
00:28:29,525 --> 00:28:32,093
that my father
became a silhouette

534
00:28:32,224 --> 00:28:34,705
when they dragged him outside.

535
00:28:39,710 --> 00:28:43,409
And then, there was this pop,

536
00:28:43,539 --> 00:28:46,542
like a firecracker,

537
00:28:46,673 --> 00:28:48,936
and the silhouette fell down.

538
00:28:51,199 --> 00:28:52,940
Oh, my God.

539
00:28:55,508 --> 00:28:58,729
The point is,

540
00:28:58,859 --> 00:29:01,514
there are always going to
be monsters in the world.

541
00:29:01,644 --> 00:29:03,516
It doesn't matter
where you are.

542
00:29:03,646 --> 00:29:05,692
But I promised myself

543
00:29:05,823 --> 00:29:08,695
I would never let them
scare the life out of me.

544
00:29:08,826 --> 00:29:11,480
-Oh, hey, hi.
-Hi!

545
00:29:12,438 --> 00:29:14,527
Ah, yeah, you just
look too dry. Come here!

546
00:29:14,657 --> 00:29:17,704
Oh, no, no, no!
No, no, no, no!

547
00:29:17,835 --> 00:29:20,141
[Ellis] Come on. Come on.
Come on. Yup, we're goin'!

548
00:29:20,272 --> 00:29:22,143
We're goin'! Hey!

549
00:29:22,274 --> 00:29:24,015
[Fatima]
Julie, come on!

550
00:29:24,145 --> 00:29:25,538
Come on!

551
00:29:25,668 --> 00:29:28,541
[Metal squeaking]

552
00:29:31,326 --> 00:29:32,371
That's the most like himself

553
00:29:32,501 --> 00:29:34,242
I've seen Ethan
since the accident.

554
00:29:34,373 --> 00:29:36,462
[Metal squeaking]

555
00:29:36,592 --> 00:29:38,594
How long have you lived here?

556
00:29:38,725 --> 00:29:41,293
Just a few months.

557
00:29:41,423 --> 00:29:43,425
Mom and Dad are trying to
figure out where we are

558
00:29:43,556 --> 00:29:45,210
so we can all go home.

559
00:29:45,340 --> 00:29:47,603
That's what
the Cromenockle would do.

560
00:29:47,734 --> 00:29:49,518
What's a Cromenockle?

561
00:29:49,649 --> 00:29:53,174
[Tabitha]
She's a sweet girl.

562
00:29:56,308 --> 00:29:58,136
Hey, honey.
Don't make her sit there.

563
00:29:58,266 --> 00:29:59,877
Those things are filthy.

564
00:30:00,007 --> 00:30:03,315
It's okay.
It's... it's actually kinda fun.

565
00:30:03,445 --> 00:30:07,145
Sara said we can go see the
goats and chickens at the barn.

566
00:30:07,275 --> 00:30:08,799
Really?

567
00:30:08,929 --> 00:30:10,888
My brother, he tends to all
the animals for the town.

568
00:30:11,018 --> 00:30:12,628
I thought it might
be fun to show Ethan.

569
00:30:12,759 --> 00:30:14,630
It's just down the street.

570
00:30:14,761 --> 00:30:17,416
Do you want to go?
I'm gonna tell Dad we're going.

571
00:30:17,546 --> 00:30:19,505
[Sara]
I can take him.

572
00:30:19,635 --> 00:30:20,593
I don't want to
take you guys away

573
00:30:20,723 --> 00:30:22,421
from anything
that you're doing.

574
00:30:22,551 --> 00:30:24,640
We're not doing anything.
Hey, Jim,

575
00:30:24,771 --> 00:30:26,425
I'll be right back.

576
00:30:26,555 --> 00:30:28,340
Okay.

577
00:30:32,605 --> 00:30:37,392
[Birds chirping]

578
00:30:41,266 --> 00:30:43,137
Hey, babe.

579
00:30:44,704 --> 00:30:47,315
It's been a while.

580
00:30:47,446 --> 00:30:50,797
Things have been...

581
00:30:50,928 --> 00:30:54,192
they've been a little
crazy past few days.

582
00:30:54,322 --> 00:30:57,499
Those, uh, things...

583
00:30:57,630 --> 00:31:00,851
they, uh...

584
00:31:00,981 --> 00:31:04,724
they got into the house
where the little girl lived,

585
00:31:04,855 --> 00:31:07,466
got into the clinic.

586
00:31:08,728 --> 00:31:11,252
You know, we were doing
pretty good for a while there,

587
00:31:11,383 --> 00:31:12,863
keeping everything together.

588
00:31:12,993 --> 00:31:14,647
It was almost
starting to feel like...

589
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:22,437
[Clears throat]

590
00:31:26,354 --> 00:31:28,879
Uh...

591
00:31:29,009 --> 00:31:33,405
I started getting tremors
in my hand a few weeks back,

592
00:31:33,535 --> 00:31:36,321
same way it started with my Dad,

593
00:31:36,451 --> 00:31:39,237
which means the clock
is officially ticking.

594
00:31:40,499 --> 00:31:44,416
But, see, uh...

595
00:31:44,546 --> 00:31:47,201
I have this crazy idea
that might actually work,

596
00:31:47,332 --> 00:31:49,464
and-and if it does,

597
00:31:49,595 --> 00:31:53,816
then I might be able to find
a way to get these people home,

598
00:31:53,947 --> 00:31:58,430
to get Ellis home.

599
00:31:58,560 --> 00:32:02,347
Of course if it doesn't,
if I'm wrong or if I fail,

600
00:32:02,477 --> 00:32:04,610
then, uh...

601
00:32:04,740 --> 00:32:06,742
then I'm leaving these people
in a worse-off position

602
00:32:06,873 --> 00:32:09,136
than they already are.

603
00:32:12,792 --> 00:32:16,578
You were always the one...
[Chuckles]

604
00:32:16,709 --> 00:32:18,711
You made all the hard calls.

605
00:32:18,841 --> 00:32:21,322
"Sometimes you got
to swing big, baby."

606
00:32:21,453 --> 00:32:23,672
[Laughs]
'Member that?

607
00:32:23,803 --> 00:32:25,587
[Laughs]

608
00:32:25,718 --> 00:32:28,242
God, you had...
[Laughs]

609
00:32:29,591 --> 00:32:31,593
[Laughs]

610
00:32:33,595 --> 00:32:36,598
[Stammers] I do this

611
00:32:36,729 --> 00:32:38,861
and that's about as big
a swing as I can take.

612
00:32:38,992 --> 00:32:41,734
And, um...

613
00:32:41,864 --> 00:32:44,128
And look, I know,
I know, I always said

614
00:32:44,258 --> 00:32:48,523
that I don't believe in signs
or any of that stuff, but...

615
00:32:51,048 --> 00:32:53,615
I could really use
one right now, okay?

616
00:32:55,922 --> 00:32:59,752
'Cause, babe,
I'm standing at the plate,

617
00:32:59,882 --> 00:33:02,276
and I'll swing if you
tell me to swing. I just...

618
00:33:07,064 --> 00:33:08,630
Babe, I just need
a little help here.

619
00:33:08,761 --> 00:33:10,241
Come on.

620
00:33:11,590 --> 00:33:13,461
I need a sign.

621
00:33:13,592 --> 00:33:15,463
[Birds chirping]

622
00:33:21,469 --> 00:33:23,297
Father Khatri?

623
00:33:25,734 --> 00:33:27,736
Nathan.

624
00:33:27,867 --> 00:33:30,391
Have you come up here much?

625
00:33:30,522 --> 00:33:32,567
No, not really.

626
00:33:32,698 --> 00:33:34,308
It's strange,
don't you think?

627
00:33:34,439 --> 00:33:37,790
A place like this...

628
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:41,228
could exist in
a place like this?

629
00:33:43,752 --> 00:33:46,799
Um...

630
00:33:46,929 --> 00:33:50,890
I was wondering,
what are the rules?

631
00:33:51,021 --> 00:33:55,547
When it comes to confession,

632
00:33:55,677 --> 00:33:58,941
if I tell you something,

633
00:33:59,072 --> 00:34:00,682
does it stay between
the two of us?

634
00:34:00,813 --> 00:34:03,337
Anything you tell me
stays between us and God.

635
00:34:04,643 --> 00:34:06,514
What if it's bad?

636
00:34:08,690 --> 00:34:10,562
What if it's really bad?

637
00:34:12,868 --> 00:34:13,826
That one's name
is Alma.

638
00:34:13,956 --> 00:34:14,914
Hi, Alma.

639
00:34:15,045 --> 00:34:16,959
[Tabitha chuckles]

640
00:34:17,090 --> 00:34:18,787
Oh, this is so much fun.
Thank you.

641
00:34:18,918 --> 00:34:20,963
It's my pleasure.

642
00:34:21,094 --> 00:34:23,662
Really,
he's a little sweetheart.

643
00:34:25,620 --> 00:34:26,926
Yeah.

644
00:34:27,057 --> 00:34:29,320
You have
a really nice family.

645
00:34:29,450 --> 00:34:31,409
Hmm.

646
00:34:32,932 --> 00:34:35,500
It's okay to be sad,
you know?

647
00:34:37,763 --> 00:34:39,286
And it's okay
to be afraid.

648
00:34:42,985 --> 00:34:44,552
Yeah, it seems the one thing

649
00:34:44,683 --> 00:34:46,685
that everyone
in this town agrees on.

650
00:34:48,904 --> 00:34:50,863
Really, though,
you'd be surprised

651
00:34:50,993 --> 00:34:53,518
how quickly
all this becomes normal.

652
00:34:57,739 --> 00:35:01,482
I don't want this
to become normal.

653
00:35:01,613 --> 00:35:03,658
I just want
to go back home.

654
00:35:04,790 --> 00:35:05,791
Me too.

655
00:35:08,837 --> 00:35:10,709
At least we have
the talismans, though.

656
00:35:10,839 --> 00:35:12,537
Father Khatri
always talks about

657
00:35:12,667 --> 00:35:13,886
how much worse
it was for people.

658
00:35:14,016 --> 00:35:16,584
They'd just hide
in places after dark,

659
00:35:16,715 --> 00:35:19,544
hoping the monsters
wouldn't find them.

660
00:35:19,674 --> 00:35:21,111
Those hiding places
are all over town.

661
00:35:21,241 --> 00:35:23,809
It's really good
to know about them,

662
00:35:23,939 --> 00:35:26,464
just in case you ever
get stuck outside after dark.

663
00:35:26,594 --> 00:35:28,640
Yeah, I guess.

664
00:35:28,770 --> 00:35:30,903
There's one in the barn.
I can show you where it is.

665
00:35:31,033 --> 00:35:32,861
Really?

666
00:35:32,992 --> 00:35:35,125
Yeah, it's just...
It's right inside.

667
00:35:37,692 --> 00:35:38,824
Uh, yeah.

668
00:35:41,131 --> 00:35:44,482
Honey, uh, I'll be right back,
okay? Don't move.

669
00:35:44,612 --> 00:35:45,787
[Sara] This way.

670
00:35:56,233 --> 00:36:00,106
Nathan, you should've
come to me much sooner.

671
00:36:00,237 --> 00:36:02,587
I didn't...
Wait, wait.

672
00:36:02,717 --> 00:36:03,979
What's gonna happen to her?

673
00:36:04,110 --> 00:36:05,807
[Stammers] I don't want
her to go in the box.

674
00:36:05,938 --> 00:36:07,505
You gave your word.

675
00:36:07,635 --> 00:36:09,246
And I intend to keep it.

676
00:36:09,376 --> 00:36:11,726
But right now, we have to worry
about the people of the town.

677
00:36:11,857 --> 00:36:13,032
She'll be at the diner.

678
00:36:13,163 --> 00:36:15,556
Okay. Come on.
Let's go.

679
00:36:15,687 --> 00:36:27,481
♪

680
00:36:44,106 --> 00:36:45,586
People used to spend
the night in here?

681
00:36:47,197 --> 00:36:48,763
What are you doing?
Sara!

682
00:36:48,894 --> 00:36:50,809
-Sorry, Tabitha.
-[Tabitha] Open up!

683
00:36:50,939 --> 00:36:52,637
I'm sorry.
I'm doing this for you.

684
00:36:52,767 --> 00:36:54,029
I'm doing this
for all of us.

685
00:36:54,160 --> 00:36:56,728
Why are you sorry?
Just open the door, please!

686
00:36:56,858 --> 00:36:58,773
-I'm sorry.
-[Tabitha] Sara!

687
00:36:58,904 --> 00:37:01,950
Sara! Sara!

688
00:37:05,867 --> 00:37:07,652
Go get your sister.

689
00:37:10,002 --> 00:37:11,525
Father Khatri!

690
00:37:15,007 --> 00:37:18,489
Hey, I've got kind of
a weird question for you.

691
00:37:18,619 --> 00:37:21,753
If, uh...

692
00:37:21,883 --> 00:37:26,061
If someone asked for a sign,

693
00:37:26,192 --> 00:37:29,021
how would they know
what they were looking for?

694
00:37:33,243 --> 00:37:34,592
Sara?

695
00:37:34,722 --> 00:37:35,984
Looking for your sister?

696
00:37:36,115 --> 00:37:37,159
Yeah.

697
00:37:37,290 --> 00:37:38,944
She's not here.

698
00:37:39,074 --> 00:37:40,815
I saw her heading
towards the barn

699
00:37:40,946 --> 00:37:41,903
with that Matthews lady
and her boy.

700
00:37:43,992 --> 00:37:47,169
[Goats bleating]

701
00:37:47,300 --> 00:37:50,477
[Goats bleating]

702
00:37:55,743 --> 00:38:00,487
[Goats bleating]

703
00:38:03,925 --> 00:38:05,797
Where's my mom?

704
00:38:05,927 --> 00:38:07,929
She'll be right out.

705
00:38:09,061 --> 00:38:10,497
Come here.

706
00:38:12,151 --> 00:38:13,587
I need to tell you something.

707
00:38:14,719 --> 00:38:16,024
Sara!

708
00:38:16,155 --> 00:38:19,114
Ethan! Sara!

709
00:38:19,245 --> 00:38:21,682
I really like you.

710
00:38:21,813 --> 00:38:23,989
And what's about to happen,

711
00:38:24,119 --> 00:38:27,297
it's gonna save everyone,

712
00:38:27,427 --> 00:38:30,996
just like in one
of your stories.

713
00:38:31,126 --> 00:38:32,954
You're gonna be the hero.

714
00:38:35,348 --> 00:38:36,523
Where's my Mom?
I want my Mom!

715
00:38:36,654 --> 00:38:39,961
-We're doing this for her!
-[Nathan] Sara!

716
00:38:40,092 --> 00:38:41,920
-Sara, what are you doing?
-This is how we go home.

717
00:38:42,050 --> 00:38:43,225
Let him go.

718
00:38:43,356 --> 00:38:45,140
They told me,
this was the last one,

719
00:38:45,271 --> 00:38:46,751
then everyone gets to go home!

720
00:38:46,881 --> 00:38:49,014
Ethan! Sara!

721
00:38:50,885 --> 00:38:52,713
-[Grunts]
-[Nathan] Ethan, run!

722
00:38:52,844 --> 00:38:55,107
[Screams]
No! Let me go!

723
00:38:55,237 --> 00:38:57,588
You don't understand!

724
00:38:59,329 --> 00:39:02,027
Oh, my God, Ethan! Ethan!

725
00:39:02,157 --> 00:39:03,811
-[Gasps]
-[Sara] Nathan?

726
00:39:05,204 --> 00:39:07,075
Nathan?

727
00:39:07,206 --> 00:39:08,860
Nathan!

728
00:39:08,990 --> 00:39:09,904
[Gasps]

729
00:39:10,035 --> 00:39:12,124
No!

730
00:39:12,254 --> 00:39:13,778
No, Nathan!

731
00:39:13,908 --> 00:39:15,606
-Nathan.
-[Sara] Nathan, please!

732
00:39:15,736 --> 00:39:17,129
Nathan!

733
00:39:17,259 --> 00:39:18,913
Nathan! Nathan!

734
00:39:20,915 --> 00:39:21,829
Nathan! No!

735
00:39:21,960 --> 00:39:24,702
My God, please!

736
00:39:24,832 --> 00:39:26,573
Please, Nath...

737
00:39:34,494 --> 00:39:37,062
You guys are right.
It's not all bad here.

738
00:39:37,192 --> 00:39:39,847
[Giggles]

739
00:39:39,978 --> 00:39:42,067
You know, I was thinking,
when we get back to the house...

740
00:39:42,197 --> 00:39:43,242
-[Ethan] Julie!
-What?

741
00:39:43,373 --> 00:39:44,722
[Sobbing]

742
00:39:44,852 --> 00:39:46,158
Hey. Ethan?

743
00:39:46,288 --> 00:39:47,377
-[Ellis] Hey.
-[Ethan] Julie!

744
00:39:47,507 --> 00:39:49,117
Hey, hey, hey.
What's wrong?

745
00:39:49,248 --> 00:39:50,771
-Where's Mom and Dad?
-[Crying]

746
00:39:50,902 --> 00:39:52,207
Hey, what's wrong?

747
00:39:52,338 --> 00:39:53,687
It's okay. Don't cry.

748
00:39:53,818 --> 00:39:56,908
Come here. Come here.
Come here. It's okay. Shh.

749
00:39:57,038 --> 00:39:57,735
[Voices screaming]

750
00:39:57,865 --> 00:40:00,259
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

751
00:40:00,390 --> 00:40:01,652
Oh, my God! Ethan!

752
00:40:01,782 --> 00:40:03,001
Tabitha!

753
00:40:03,131 --> 00:40:04,089
Ethan!

754
00:40:05,264 --> 00:40:06,961
[Banging]
[Tabitha] Help me!

755
00:40:07,092 --> 00:40:09,268
Please help me!

756
00:40:09,399 --> 00:40:10,835
Help me out here, please!

757
00:40:10,965 --> 00:40:12,140
[Jim] Tabitha!

758
00:40:12,271 --> 00:40:13,228
Tabitha!

759
00:40:13,359 --> 00:40:15,143
Jim! Jim, over here!

760
00:40:15,274 --> 00:40:17,102
You okay?

761
00:40:17,232 --> 00:40:18,277
Where... where's Ethan?

762
00:40:18,408 --> 00:40:19,713
-What?
-Where's Ethan?!

763
00:40:19,844 --> 00:40:21,715
Go and find him!

764
00:40:21,846 --> 00:40:22,890
[Indistinct chatter]

765
00:40:23,021 --> 00:40:25,632
[Jim]
Ethan! Ethan!

766
00:40:25,763 --> 00:40:26,981
Jim!

767
00:40:27,112 --> 00:40:28,330
-[Julie] Mom!
-Jim, where's Ethan!?

768
00:40:28,461 --> 00:40:29,854
-[Julie] Dad!
-I don't know.

769
00:40:29,984 --> 00:40:31,072
-Where's Ethan?
-[Julie] Mom!

770
00:40:31,203 --> 00:40:33,205
Oh, my God! Ethan.

771
00:40:33,335 --> 00:40:34,772
-Oh, my God!
-[Ellis] Here you go.

772
00:40:34,902 --> 00:40:35,860
Oh, my God!

773
00:40:37,383 --> 00:40:38,950
Come here, come here.

774
00:40:39,080 --> 00:40:40,778
[Gasps]

775
00:40:40,908 --> 00:40:51,223
♪

776
00:40:58,926 --> 00:41:02,756
[Breathing heavily]

777
00:41:12,549 --> 00:41:13,854
-I was too late.
-Hold on.

778
00:41:13,985 --> 00:41:15,073
-I'm sorry.
-Hey.

779
00:41:15,203 --> 00:41:16,683
Jim. Tabitha.

780
00:41:18,163 --> 00:41:20,252
[Sighing]

781
00:41:20,382 --> 00:41:21,775
-How is he?
-He's fine. He's fine.

782
00:41:21,906 --> 00:41:24,082
-We're gonna go home.
-[Jim] You go on ahead, okay?

783
00:41:24,212 --> 00:41:25,866
-Come on, Jules.
-I'll catch up.

784
00:41:29,261 --> 00:41:31,481
Where is she?

785
